One of my favorite things about my job is that no week or day is ever the same. It's always different and fun, but also means I need lots of energy and to be ready for anything. Thanks to this delicious @MakeItMiO liquid water enhancer I am motivated throughout the day with the electrolytes added to my water by MiO Electrolytes! I especially love the yummy grape flavor, it's so delicious! 🍇💗 It truly helps me feel like I can go from waking up, to the gym, home to get ready for the day, emails and editing, head to the city for a shoot at the farmers market, more shooting in Chinatown, and then take the subway home to have dinner with a friend.

Most mornings of the week I enjoy a delicious acai bowl with @ZICOCoconut 😋 I always get asked what I put in them and typically it is: 2 bananas, 5 strawberries, 1-2 packs of acai frozen, a few table spoons of Zico Coconut water, and perhaps a little bit of almond butter or chia seeds! Seriously such a yummy way to start the day.

Literally walking down memory lane at the @refinery29 X @girlshbo exhibition and am seriously getting so nostalgic ❤ this show started shortly after I moved to Brooklyn and has been something I've watched season after season and has really captured living in Brooklyn as a 20 something so accurately to me. I'm sad it's over but today and tomorrow you can visit the exhibition and relive all of the best moments! I really got teary eyed

Merry Christmas to all of you!!! 🎅🏻 Santa came and visited us and Diego and I are so excited 🐶 I hope you are having a great day celebrating your holiday with those that you love ❤️ and keeping those in your heart that aren't surrounded by loved ones or as fortunate as yourself. There's been times after my dad passed away and I moved to NYC that I was all alone on Christmas and had disconnected from family for a long time. I'm happy to say that isn't where I am at now, but every Christmas hasn't always been presents and laughter. Sometimes you have to work through the tough stuff to eventually get to the happy, but I promise it's worth it. So whatever your circumstances are,
I hope you have a full heart today ❤️

I want to be super honest with you guys and share with you that I didn't vote in the last election. It's something I've regretted for a long time. I was confused at the age of 18 about so many different issues, who was better for the job, and sadly just the fear of voting, being in a booth, and not knowing what to do when I was in the booth. I was scared to reach out and ask someone for help or ask for advice about understanding different issues. Which is crazy because who knows how to do anything unless they ask for help?! So this is my message for you guys- please get out and vote! This year it is so important and the future of our amazing country is in your hands. Don't be like 18 year old me and be afraid- get out and ask for help and advice! Do your research and read up on facts and issues. I love that @TOMS created this awesome Step Out and Vote tote to inspire others and promote voting!

Something you guys don't know about me is when I was in grade school, I had to transfer to different schools twice due to others bullying me. It was heartbreaking and something no teen should even have to go through. 1 in 4 youth report that they have been bullyied and that just breaks my heart because I've been there. I've teamed up with @PlanetFitness because during the month of October they will be promoting their pro-kindness/anti-bullying initiative, the Judgement Free Generation.Now through October 13, they are hosting a promotion in which for every new member join, Planet Fitness will donate all enrollment fees to BGCA (last year, they donated more than $1 million!) My mother who passed when I was younger loved the Boys and Girls Clubs of America and did a lot to help our local clubs, so this is something that's even more near and dear to my heart due to that. Click the link in my bio to learn more about this initiative and get involved!

I tend to hide behind things, particularly my hair and clothing. Over the past 6 months I've really tried to work on 'me' and feeling comfortable in my own skin. You know the memes you see where it's a photo of a celeb crying and the caption is something like "You thought you had $5 in your bank account, but turns out you have negative $20"? I HAVE BEEN THERE! I've been the girl eating ramen for a week and struggling to even have enough money to take the subway to work.. one of the worst parts is I felt like I had to hide that and couldn't ask my friends for advice on how to better save for my future. I was embarrassed and didn't know what I was doing honestly. Now I've learned more from deciding to be open and talking to my friends and family about how to better my future financially and I still feel like I have so much to learn! 💗
Can you imagine how powerful it would be to freely talk about money and it not be a taboo? @IntuitTurbo has changed the game to help us learn for a better future.

Giving my lil bun a kiss 💋🐰 Happy almost Easter everyone! Wanted to take a second to remind anyone out there whos been thinking of getting a bunny as a pet or for their kids that they are a huge responsibility and in some ways even more so than a dog. You have to bunny proof your home, they need fresh hay available 24/7, clean their litter box nearly every other day, fresh water, fresh veggies twice a day (the right ones), litter trained (mine is) and I personally am a strong believer in only having your bunnies live indoors, not out. My bunny Monty is truly like a child to me. Rabbits deserve the same love and care you would give a puppy, except they are even more delicate and fragile. Honestly a bunny is only right for a family if you're going to teach everyone in your home how careful you have to be and how to love and care for them properly. Also if you do decide a bunny is right for you- adopt don't shop please! There are so many bunnies that get brought in (especially this time of the year) that need loving homes! ❤️

I wanted to take a moment and talk about something a little different today. As a blogger, sometimes it can be a little scary talking about something that could be controversial,but I believe in using my voice to talk about things I truly do believe in!
